ler Verflechtung, von der Kiezkneipe bis zur Oper, vom Zirkus bis zu neuem Tanzvergnügen. Es geht um Orte und Akteure, Handlungsformen und Wissenstransfer. Berlin steht im Mittelpunkt, doch europäische Vergleiche und Verflechtungen treten ebenso hervor wie globale Netzwerke.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aAmusementszEuropexHistoryvCongresses. 0aCity and town lifezEuropexHistoryvCongresses. 0aMetropolitan areaszEuropexHistoryvCongresses. 0aPopular culturezEuropexHistoryvCongresses. 0aPopular culturezGermanyzBerlinxHistoryvCongresses. 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh  aKulturgeschichte, Metropolenkultur, Stadtgeschichte.1 aBecker, Tobias, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHochmuth, Hanno, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHolsten, Henning, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKirschnick, Sylke, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLange, Kerstin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMaase, Kaspar, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMarx, Peter W., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMüller, Sven Oliver, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNiedbalski, Johanna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNolte, Paul, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNolte, Paul, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aWarstat, Matthias, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2015z9783110439687oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2015z9783